Description: The package is created for managers, servers, and bartenders at a restaurant. 
    The main goal of this package is to create a restaurant system, complete with daily 
    check-out reports, the ability to clock in and out, and create the menu. Additionally, 
    owners and managers can create a monthly report displaying restaurant sales. Through 
    the monthly sales reports, managers can establish which months are busiest in the 
    restaurant. Understanding the busiest times of the year allow the managers to prepare 
    for these times by hiring more staff and ordering more inventory. The package provides 
    BLANK unique functions for the restaurant. The packages uses BLANK external libraries 
    or dependencies, such as devtools, ggplot2, methods, and BLANK. 
Depends: R (>= 3.1.2)
Imports: ggplot2, dplyr, devtools, methods
